What do you do when someone hands you a grocery bag filled with apples? Especially a bag of Arkansas Blacks. Pies and sauce come imediately to mind, but this crisp has to be included in the list. So easy. I used fresh cranberries rather than dried, added about 1/3 cup sugar to the apples, as well as the juice and zest of 1 lemon, and a generous 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon. This eliminated having to cook the dried berries. I too doubled the topping recipe, as one reviewer said, "That's the best part." As a close friend said, "Oh! That's a keeper!"

