Rating: 4
All of the previous posts have it right! This is an outstanding base recipe. Based on many other comments, I changed a multitude of things... 1/2 cup real apple cider and 1/2 cup water to rehydrate the cranberries. I didn't have a cinnamon stick...so I sprinkled a bit of cinnamon over them, along with some allspice. I doubled the topping but used 2/3 c flour and 2/3 cup oats..then followed others' lead and did some lemon juice and cinnamon over granny smith apples v. mcintosh. This is the most delicious crisp I've ever had! Perfect balance of sweet and tart ~ made it at Thanksgiving and will now make it at Christmas : )!!

Rating: 4
Delicious! I also made a few minor adjustments: First off, I didn't peel the apples (Granny Smith) and it saved a lot of time and added a subtle bite - so good. I tossed the sliced apples in a tiny bit of lemon juice (maybe 1 tsp?) and dusted the apples with cinnamon and then tossed to coat evenly. I also doubled the topping, and so glad I did, and added 1/3 cup of rolled oats. Mixed the topping in a food processor for ease. Also, this will probably sound crazy to some people, but after I had the whole thing ready to go, I sprinkled the tiniest little bit of sea salt (1/4 tsp maybe) over the topping to give it that sweet/savory deliciousness - and boy did it work! Fantastic contrast yet so complimenting! Will definitely make again!

